div.p:


The Ditenion and Swelling of the Belly,
with a Noie and Griping in the Guts;
and mall Looenees which return frequently.

TAke a Spoonful of Roe, and of Plantain-Water;
drop the Mixture into the Corner
of the Eye, and keep your Eye hut.

PUT a little Saffron in Plantain-Water;
mix them well together; then drop it
into the Patient's Eyes.
